DescPackaging: <<
  vtefc.c uses FC_WIDTH, so we need the newer-version fontconfig2 from
  the fontconfig2-dev pkg (static-only). This causes lots of warnings
  like:
    ld: warning multiple definitions of symbol _FcAtomicNewFile
    /sw/lib/fontconfig2/lib/libfontconfig.a(fontconfig.o) private external definition of _FcAtomicNewFile in section (__TEXT,__text)
    /usr/X11R6/lib/libfontconfig.dylib(fcatomic.o) definition of _FcAtomicNewFile

  As of 2.2.3-2, the fontconfig2-dev .pc seems to be missing a needed
  -lexpat flag, so we add it explicitly. This creates lots
    symbol _XML_ParseBuffer used from dynamic library /usr/X11R6/lib/libexpat.1.dylib(xmlparse.o) not from earlier dynamic library /sw/lib/libexpat.0.dylib(xmlparse.lo)
  I guess we can't please everyone here.
<<
